# Git Branch Workflow

Before making any code changes, follow this workflow:

## 1. Create a child branch from origin/main

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout -b <branch-name> origin/main
```

Use a descriptive branch name (e.g., `feature/hydration-fix`, `fix/meal-tracking`, `feat/new-component`).

## 2. Make changes

Implement the requested changes on the new branch only.

## 3. Commit and push to the child branch

```bash
git add <changed-files>
git commit -m "<descriptive message>"
git push -u origin <branch-name>
```

## Rules

- **Never** commit directly to `main` — always work on a child branch
- **Always** branch from `origin/main` (not local main) to ensure a clean base
- **Push** to the child branch; do not merge to main unless the user explicitly asks
